CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 4, 1960, pg. 2 reads: "Three Men Die on Saturday Night Ride When Their Car Crashed Into Abutment - Death Scene - Andrew Burton's car (Right), speeding in arrow's direction (left photo), crashed with terrific force into the above abutment near Coraopolis and caused the death of Burton, his stepfather, William Wells, and a friend, Saul Davis. Burton was returning to Coraopolis after a trip to Sewickley to pick up a sister who was leaving work.  She was not in the car because another relative had driven her home. - Harris Photos"image published by Pittsburgh Courier newspaper with graphic addition of arrow.
TitMainTitle: Damaged Buick car driven by Andrew Burton after fatal crash against an abutment, Moon Township
